3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo calculates funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average price mechanism between the perpetual future and spot index. The exchange's rollup architecture enables rapid funding rate updates while maintaining decentralized settlement. Funding payments are automatically debited or credited to trader positions based on the hourly rate, with long positions paying shorts when rates are positive. Aevo's off-chain order book provides tighter spreads for ATOM perpetuals compared to purely on-chain DEXs."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ATOM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM represents the Cosmos Hub token with moderate liquidity and volatility patterns that create profitable funding rate differentials. The token's correlation with broader market movements while maintaining independent price action makes it ideal for cross-exchange arbitrage strategies. Aevo's unique positioning as a rollup-based DEX often sees funding rates diverge from centralized exchanges due to different trader demographics and liquidity profiles."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM funding rates on Aevo typically range from -0.1% to 0.3% per day, with higher volatility during Cosmos ecosystem developments or broader market stress. The 1-hour funding frequency creates more granular arbitrage windows compared to 8-hour cycles on major centralized exchanges. During IBC protocol updates or major Cosmos announcements, funding rates can spike to 1%+ daily as traders position for price movements. Weekend periods often show compressed funding rates due to lower trading activity on the rollup-based platform."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between Aevo and centralized platforms like Binance or OKX frequently yields 10-50 basis points per day due to different funding calculation methods and trader bases. Aevo's rollup infrastructure allows for faster position adjustments during funding rate convergence, providing tactical advantages for arbitrageurs. The platform's combined options and perps ecosystem creates unique hedging opportunities where traders can use ATOM options to offset perpetual funding costs. Pre-launch token markets on Aevo sometimes create temporary funding rate inefficiencies as traders position ahead of major listings."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Aevo's rollup centralization presents systemic risks not found in traditional perpetual futures platforms, with potential sequencer failures affecting funding settlements. Lower liquidity compared to tier-1 exchanges can lead to wider spreads and slippage during large arbitrage position adjustments. The platform's 0.02%/0.05% maker/taker fees must be factored into net funding rate calculations, potentially eroding thin arbitrage margins. Cross-chain bridge risks exist when moving USDT or ATOM between Aevo's rollup and other networks for arbitrage execution."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are ATOM funding rates updated on Aevo?","answer":"Aevo updates ATOM funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average price calculation. This frequent update cycle creates more arbitrage opportunities compared to exchanges with 8-hour funding periods, but requires active monitoring for optimal execution."},{"question":"What are the trading fees for ATOM perpetuals on Aevo?","answer":"Aevo charges 0.02% maker fees and 0.05% taker fees for ATOM perpetual futures. These fees apply to opening and closing positions and should be included in funding rate arbitrage profitability calculations alongside potential withdrawal costs."},{"question":"Can I use ATOM options to hedge funding rate exposure on Aevo?","answer":"Yes, Aevo's combined derivatives platform allows traders to use ATOM options for sophisticated hedging strategies. You can sell covered calls against long perpetual positions or buy protective puts to limit downside while collecting funding payments."},{"question":"How does Aevo's rollup affect ATOM funding rate accuracy?","answer":"Aevo's dedicated rollup enables faster price updates and more accurate funding rate calculations compared to congested Layer 1 networks. The off-chain order book provides real-time price discovery while on-chain settlement ensures transparent funding payments without MEV interference."}]}]
